Title: Deployment of Prometheus and Grafana on AWS EKS using Helm

1. Introduction
Prometheus and Grafana are monitoring tools used to monitor Kubernetes clusters.
Prometheus collects metrics such as CPU, memory, pods, and node usage.
Grafana visualizes these metrics through dashboards.

2. Install Helm
Helm is a package manager for Kubernetes.

Commands:
curl -fsSL -o get_helm.sh https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/main/scripts/get-helm-3
chmod 700 get_helm.sh
./get_helm.sh

3. Add Helm Repositories

helm repo add stable https://charts.helm.sh/stable
helm repo add prometheus-community https://prometheus-community.github.io/helm-charts
helm repo update

These repositories contain Helm charts for Prometheus and Grafana.

4. Create Namespace

kubectl create namespace prometheus

Namespace helps organize Kubernetes resources.

5. Install Prometheus and Grafana

helm install stable prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack -n prometheus

This command installs:
- Prometheus
- Grafana
- Alertmanager
- Node Exporter
- kube-state-metrics

6. Check Running Pods

kubectl get pods -n prometheus

7. Check Services

kubectl get svc -n prometheus

8. Expose Prometheus Service

kubectl edit svc stable-kube-prometheus-sta-prometheus -n prometheus

Change service type to:
NodePort

9. Expose Grafana Service

kubectl edit svc stable-grafana -n prometheus

Change service type to:
NodePort

10. Get Grafana Password

kubectl get secret --namespace prometheus stable-grafana -o jsonpath="{.data.admin-password}" | base64 --decode ; echo

Default username: admin

11. Access Grafana Dashboard

Open in browser:

http://<Node-IP>:<NodePort>

Grafana dashboards show:
- Pod CPU usage
- Pod memory usage
- Node metrics
- Cluster health

12. Monitoring Architecture

AWS EKS Cluster
      ↓
Node Exporter + kube-state-metrics
      ↓
Prometheus (collects metrics)
      ↓
Grafana (visualizes metrics)

13. Benefits

- Real-time monitoring
- Resource usage tracking
- Performance analysis
- Cluster health monitoring
